ANC Secretary General Gwede Mantashe says the NWC has no doubt that the new ministers will work with integrity, dedication &amp; humility to serve SA. JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) Secretary General Gwede Mantashe says the party is firmly behind the new Finance Minister Malusi Gigaba and the rest of the new ministers appointed in the recent Cabinet reshuffle.The party held a briefing earlier on Wednesday following the National Working Committee (NWC) meeting on Tuesday.Mantashe says the committee has no doubt that the new ministers will work with integrity, dedication and humility to serve the country. The unfortunate event that transpired following their appointment should not disturb from the fact that the individual and collectively are capable comrades who have invaluable skills and experience to offer to the work of government. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)